[SN]TITLE[SN]
Future of mid Wales healthcare services discussed

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
The future of healthcare in mid Wales is being discussed at a series of meetings.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
The first took place in Machynlleth on Monday, where more than 70 people talked about Bronglais Hospital, mental health and community services.
Another three will take place in Powys and Ceredigion in February.
The Mid Wales Healthcare Collaborative has organised the gatherings to give people a chance to influence the future of health services.
